 for bestpractices and # Client Portal (No-login) Experience

## Overview
Develop a secure, tokenized client experience that enables clients to review, compare, comment on, and approve design decisions without requiring a login. Each shareable link is time-limited and scoped to specific projects/decisions. The system records client actions, maps them to identities when provided, supports link revocation and analytics, and provides two primary pages: a decision detail view and a mobile-first client portal view accessible via a signed URL. The solution emphasizes a low-friction, visually rich, decision-centric workflow aligned with Archject’s design ethos.

## Components to Build
- Tokenized Client Link Generator
  - Generates per-shareable-link tokens with signed, time-limited validity
  - Scopes tokens to specific project, decision(s), and permissions (view, comment, approve, export)
  - Includes revocation mechanism and analytics hooks
- Client Portal (No-Login Link) Page
  - Mobile-first, responsive view rendered from a tokenized URL
  - Lists Decision Cards with visual comparison and quick actions
  - Commenting, decision options comparison, and approval workflow
  - Client-side UI for reviewing attachments, notes, and progress
- Decision Detail Page
  - Full view of a single Decision Card
  - Visual side-by-side comparison of options
  - Rich comments thread, approval status, historical timeline
  - Attachments viewer (drawings, specs, PDFs, images)
  - Actions: share, export, create follow-up task
  - Audit trail: time-stamped actions, who performed actions (if identity provided)
- Link Analytics & Revocation Console
  - Dashboard for link usage, view counts, time-to-approve, last access
  - Ability to revoke individual links or adjust expiration
- Backend Services
  - Token generation, validation, and revocation
  - Permissions enforcement per token
  - Action mapping to user context (when a user identity is present)
  - Data export pipelines for decisions/logs
  - Notification/reminder scheduling hooks (optional, for follow-ups)
- Data Persistency
  - Projects, Decisions, Options, Attachments, Comments, Approvals
  - Token records, link metadata, and analytics events
  - Lightweight audit logs for compliance

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- UI Frameworks: Adopt project’s design system. Use a modern component library (or custom components) with accessible ARIA attributes.
- Pages and Routes
  - page_client_portal: Route for the tokenized host-facing portal
  - page_decision_detail: Route for the full decision detail view (may be opened within client portal iframe-like flow or directly via tokenized link)
- Core UI Components
  - Decision Card: Visual comparison (side-by-side options), key metrics, status badge, comments snippet, attachments preview, actions row
  - Option Comparison Panel: Responsive grid with images/specs, toggle between options, highlight differences
  - Comments Thread: Inline threaded comments, mentions, and client-friendly input
  - Approval Control: Clear approve/decline with optional comment, timestamped confirmation
  - Attachments Viewer: Inline viewer for PDFs/images, download/export options
  - Action Buttons: Share, Export (PDF/CSV), Create Follow-up Task
  - Navbar/Top Bar: Minimal chrome with brand, and a subtle progress indicator
  - Sidebar (for internal navigation in designer/studio view): Only if the client portal shares a workspace with staff
  - Token Status Indicator: Visual cue for token validity, expiration, and revocation
- Responsiveness & Interaction
  - Mobile-first layout with progressive enhancement for larger viewports
  - Keyboard accessibility: Tab order, focus management, and high-contrast states
  - Animations: Subtle, non-disruptive micro-interactions for hover, focus, and state changes
- Data Handling
  - Fetch decision and related data using token-scoped endpoints
  - Persist client actions (comments, approvals) via token-authenticated requests
  - Local caching for quick UI updates with a solid optimistic UI pattern

### Backend
- Services
  - Token Service
    - Generate signed tokens with: project_id, decision_id(s), allowed_actions, expiry, and a unique token id
    - Verify token on each request; enforce time window and scope
    - Revoke tokens (per-link revocation) and track last-used metadata
  - Decision & Option Service
    - Retrieve decision data, options, visual assets, and attachments
    - Compute and serve side-by-side comparisons
  - Comments & Approvals Service
    - Create/read comments associated with a decision and client token
    - Record approvals (with optional client-provided notes)
  - Attachments Service
    - Serve secure pre-signed URLs for attachments
  - Analytics & Audit Service
    - Record token views, actions (comment, approve, export), and timestamps
    - Provide aggregated analytics per link
  - Export Service
    - Generate export artifacts (PDF/CSV) of decision details and logs
  - Notification/Reminder Service (optional)
    - Schedule nudges to clients if allowed by token scope
- Data Models
  - Tokens: token_id, token, project_id, decision_ids[], actions[], expires_at, revoked, created_at, last_used_at, client_identity_hint
  - Projects: project_id, name, brand_id, workspace settings
  - Decisions: decision_id, project_id, title, description, status, created_at, updated_at, attachments
  - Options: option_id, decision_id, name, visuals (image/video links), specs, pricing/metrics
  - Comments: comment_id, decision_id, token_id, user_identity (nullable), text, created_at, attachments
  - Approvals: approval_id, decision_id, token_id, approved (boolean), comment, created_at
  - Attachments: attachment_id, decision_id, type, url, name, size, created_at
  - Analytics: event_id, token_id, event_type (view/comment/approve/export), timestamp, ip_address (anonymized), user_agent, locale
- APIs & Endpoints
  - POST /api/token/generate
    - Body: project_id, decision_ids[], allowed_actions, expiry_minutes
    - Response: { token_id, token, expires_at, decision_ids }
  - GET /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}
    - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
    - Response: decision payload (title, options, comparison data, comments, attachments, status)
  - POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/comment
    - Headers: Bearer token
    - Body: text, optional attachments
  - POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/approve
    - Headers: Bearer token
    - Body: approved: boolean, optional comment
  - GET /api/portal/link/{token_id}
    - Headers: Optional token
    - Response: token metadata, validity, scope, usage analytics
  - POST /api/portal/link/{token_id}/revoke
  - GET /api/portal/analytics/{token_id}
  - GET /api/portal/export/{decision_id}
    - Generates and returns export artifact (PDF/CSV)
- Security
  - Token-based access; no user login required
  - Scope-limited permissions per token (view, comment, approve, export)
  - Time-limited tokens with expiry; revocation supported
  - Server-side validation of token before data fetch or action
  - Data minimization: do not reveal internal user identities unless identity is provided via token context
  - Rate limiting and IP-based anomaly detection for abuse prevention
- Validation
  - Input Validation: sanitize all inputs; enforce length, allowed characters, and required fields
  - Decision/Option data integrity: ensure options exist for the decision; non-empty attachments where required
  - Attachment size/type checks; accept only supported types
  - Comments: disallow disallowed content and enforce max length
  - Approvals: ensure action is permitted by token scope and decision state
- Observability
  - Structured logging for token generation, token usage, and actions
  - Metrics: token views, approvals, comments, exports per link
  - Error handling with meaningful error codes and user-friendly messages

## Integration

- Client Portal Flow
  - The tokenized URL loads page_client_portal with a token in the URL (path or query param)
  - Frontend calls backend /api/portal/decision/{decision_id} (or batch fetch) using the token for authentication
  - User reviews Decision Cards, compares options via the Decision Detail/Comparison UI
  - User adds comments or approves; requests are sent to /portal/decision endpoints with the same token
  - Actions are logged to Analytics; UI reflects real-time status through optimistic updates and periodic refresh
- Decision Detail Page
  - Renders a detailed view of a single decision with all options, history, attachments, and action controls
  - Supports export and share actions that utilize export endpoints
- Link Revocation & Analytics
  - Revoking a link updates the token's revoked flag, invalidates subsequent requests
  - Analytics page reads from Analytics service to provide usage insights
- Data Flows
  - Read path: token verification -> fetch decision data -> render
  - Write path: token verification -> record comment/approval -> update decision state -> push analytics
- Security Boundary Alignment
  - Ensure internal APIs are protected; token validation is centralized
  - Ensure no leakage of internal system URLs or IDs through the client portal
  - Compliance with data ownership and privacy requirements

## User Experience Flow

1. Share a tokenized link with a client for a specific project/decision
2. Client opens the link on mobile or desktop
3. Token is verified; if valid, the Client Portal loads with a responsive dashboard of decisions
4. Client views a Decision Card, toggles between options in a side-by-side comparison
5. Client leaves comments on options or the decision, with optional attachments
6. Client approves or declines the decision, optionally adding a clarifying comment
7. System records the action, updates approval status, and sends optional reminders or exports
8. Client can view a summary/export of the decision or share via export
9. Firm users can revoke the link or view analytics on link usage

Step-by-step flow for Decision Detail Page:
- Load: Certified token validates and fetches decision payload
- Visuals: Render decision title, status badge, and a matrix comparing Options A/B/C with visuals
- History: Display timestamped actions (comments, approvals) with contributor labels if provided
- Attachments: Show previews for drawings/specs; provide download/export
- Actions: Provide Share, Export, Create Follow-up Task
- Feedback Loop: Client can add a new comment; system updates in real-time

Step-by-step flow for Client Portal (No-login Link):
- Open: Token verification occurs; if valid, render mobile-first UI
- Decision Cards: Grid of Decision Cards with titles, status, and quick actions
- Compare: Tap to open Decision Detail for in-depth review
- Comment/Approve: Enter text comment, attach files if allowed, submit approval
- Exit: Token expires or is revoked; UI displays expiry/revocation status and limits further actions

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema Details (JSON-ish representations)
- Tokens
  - token_id: string (UUID)
  - token: string (signed token payload)
  - project_id: string
  - decision_ids: array<string>
  - allowed_actions: array<string> (view, comment, approve, export)
  - expires_at: timestamp
  - revoked: boolean
  - created_at: timestamp
  - last_used_at: timestamp
  - client_identity_hint: string (optional, e.g., email or anon_id)
- Projects
  - project_id: string
  - name: string
  - brand_settings: object
- Decisions
  - decision_id: string
  - project_id: string
  - title: string
  - description: string
  - status: string (e.g., pending, approved, declined)
  - created_at: timestamp
  - updated_at: timestamp
  - attachments: array<Attachment>
- Options
  - option_id: string
  - decision_id: string
  - name: string
  - visuals: array<MediaAsset> (image URLs, CAD exports)
  - specs: object
  - pricing: object
- Comments
  - comment_id: string
  - decision_id: string
  - token_id: string
  - user_identity: string (nullable)
  - text: string
  - attachments: array<Attachment>
  - created_at: timestamp
- Approvals
  - approval_id: string
  - decision_id: string
  - token_id: string
  - approved: boolean
  - comment: string
  - created_at: timestamp
- Attachments
  - attachment_id: string
  - decision_id: string
  - type: string (image/pdf/dwg/etc)
  - url: string
  - name: string
  - size: number
  - created_at: timestamp
- Analytics
  - event_id: string
  - token_id: string
  - event_type: string (view/comment/approve/export)
  - timestamp: timestamp
  - ip_address: string (hashed/anonymized)
  - user_agent: string
  - locale: string

API Endpoints
- POST /api/token/generate
  - Body: { project_id, decision_ids, allowed_actions, expires_in_minutes, client_identity_hint? }
  - Response: { token_id, token, expires_at, decision_ids }
- GET /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Response: { decision: { title, description, status, options: [{option_id, name, visuals, specs}], attachments, comments_count, approvals_count }, token_valid: boolean, expires_at }
- POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/comment
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Body: { text, attachments? }
  - Response: { comment_id, created_at, token_id }
- POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/approve
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Body: { approved: boolean, comment? }
  - Response: { approval_id, approved, created_at }
- GET /api/portal/link/{token_id}
  - Headers: Optional
  - Response: { token_id, project_id, decision_ids, expires_at, revoked, usage_stats }
- POST /api/portal/link/{token_id}/revoke
  - Response: { revoked: true }
- GET /api/portal/analytics/{token_id}
  - Response: { views, comments, approvals, exports, last_seen_at }
- GET /api/portal/export/{decision_id}
  - Response: { export_url, format, generated_at }

Security
- Authentication: Token-based; no user login required
- Authorization: Actions limited by token scope; validate at server before performing any operation
- Data exposure: Only fields allowed by token scope; minimal data sharing
- Revocation: Immediate token revocation supported; endpoints validate revoked status
- Input/output validation: Server-side strict validation; sanitize all inputs

Validation
- Ensure decision_id and option references exist
- Validate token validity and expiry at every request
- Validate attachment types and sizes
- Enforce maximum comment length and prohibited content checks

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Token-based access works without requiring a login; token is time-limited and scope-limited
- [ ] Decision Detail Page renders correctly with side-by-side option comparison, comments, attachments, and actions
- [ ] Client Portal loads from tokenized link on mobile and desktop with responsive UI
- [ ] Clients can add comments and approve; actions are recorded in analytics with correct token_id
- [ ] Token revocation immediately prevents further access; analytics reflect revocation
- [ ] Exports (PDF/CSV) generated for decisions and include relevant history
- [ ] Access-control errors present clear messages and do not leak internal data
- [ ] UI matches the design system: color palette, typography, spacing, and interactive states
- [ ] End-to-end tests cover: token generation, token usage flow, approval, commenting, export, and revocation

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Focus on clarity, minimalism, and visual decision support
- Ensure high-contrast typography and accessible controls
- Maintain consistent card hierarchy and status indicators
- Use the 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters; generous whitespace
- Maintain left-aligned text and consistent margins/paddings
- Subtle hover/focus states and smooth transitions
- Use the specified color palette for backgrounds, borders, text, and status cues

---

Visual Style

Color Palette:
- Primary background: #F7F7F9
- Secondary background: #FFFFFF
- Accent color: #0052CC
- Neutral grays:
  - #E5E7EB
  - #D1D5DB
  - #6B7280
  - #111827
- Status colors:
  - #10B981 (success/active)
  - #F59E42 (warning)
  - #EF4444 (error/declined)

Typography & Layout:
- Font family: Modern geometric sans-serif (Inter, SF Pro, etc.)
- Headings: H1 ~28px, H2 ~22px, H3 ~18px; weight 600–700
- Body: 15–16px, 400–500; high line-height
- Subt, uppercase/small-caps for labels
- Layout: 12-column grid; 24–32px gutters; clear separation between navigation, cards, content
- Left-aligned text; ample whitespace

Key Design Elements

Card Design:
- Cards: #FFFFFF; shadow 0px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); border-radius 8–12px
- Borders: #E5E7EB
- Hover: lift or tint #F3F4F6
- Hierarchy: Title top, muted secondary info, right-aligned status badge

Navigation:
- Sidebar: Permanent left; background #F5F6FA; active with highlight #E5E7EB or accent underline
- Icons: Minimal line icons; gray #6B7280; active state filled
- Top bar: White with bottom border #E5E7EB
- Collapsible folders: Smooth transitions
- Active items: Bold text, left border or dot in accent

Data Visualization:
- Charts: Minimal; accent color; muted gridlines
- Status indicators: Pills/dots in #10B981, #F59E42, #EF4444

Interactive Elements:
- Buttons: Rounded; primary filled with #0052CC, white text; secondary ghost/outline
- States: Hover shadow, active fill shift, disabled state with opacity
- Form fields: Rounded, borders #D1D5DB, focus ring
- Search bars: Full-width, rounded, left icon
- Micro-interactions: Smooth transitions on hover/focus

Design Philosophy
- Modern, minimalist, professional; calm, readable, structured
- Minimize cognitive load; quick decision-making
- Visual strategy emphasizes readability, whitespace, and clear hierarchy

Connected Pages:
- Decision Detail Page: Full view of a decision card with visual comparison, comments, history, attachments, and actions
- Client Portal (No-Login Link): Mobile-first client view via secure tokenized link; review, compare, comment, and approve without an account

