=== TASK ===
# Client Portal (No-login) Experience

## Overview
Develop a secure, tokenized client experience that enables clients to review, compare, comment on, and approve design decisions without requiring a login. Each shareable link is time-limited and scoped to specific projects/decisions. The system records client actions, maps them to identities when provided, supports link revocation and analytics, and provides two primary pages: a decision detail view and a mobile-first client portal view accessible via a signed URL. The solution emphasizes a low-friction, visually rich, decision-centric workflow aligned with Archject’s design ethos.

## Components to Build
- Tokenized Client Link Generator
  - Generates per-shareable-link tokens with signed, time-limited validity
  - Scopes tokens to specific project, decision(s), and permissions (view, comment, approve, export)
  - Includes revocation mechanism and analytics hooks
- Client Portal (No-Login Link) Page
  - Mobile-first, responsive view rendered from a tokenized URL
  - Lists Decision Cards with visual comparison and quick actions
  - Commenting, decision options comparison, and approval workflow
  - Client-side UI for reviewing attachments, notes, and progress
- Decision Detail Page
  - Full view of a single Decision Card
  - Visual side-by-side comparison of options
  - Rich comments thread, approval status, historical timeline
  - Attachments viewer (drawings, specs, PDFs, images)
  - Actions: share, export, create follow-up task
  - Audit trail: time-stamped actions, who performed actions (if identity provided)
- Link Analytics & Revocation Console
  - Dashboard for link usage, view counts, time-to-approve, last access
  - Ability to revoke individual links or adjust expiration
- Backend Services
  - Token generation, validation, and revocation
  - Permissions enforcement per token
  - Action mapping to user context (when a user identity is present)
  - Data export pipelines for decisions/logs
  - Notification/reminder scheduling hooks (optional, for follow-ups)
- Data Persistency
  - Projects, Decisions, Options, Attachments, Comments, Approvals
  - Token records, link metadata, and analytics events
  - Lightweight audit logs for compliance

