API Endpoints
- POST /api/token/generate
  - Body: { project_id, decision_ids, allowed_actions, expires_in_minutes, client_identity_hint? }
  - Response: { token_id, token, expires_at, decision_ids }
- GET /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Response: { decision: { title, description, status, options: [{option_id, name, visuals, specs}], attachments, comments_count, approvals_count }, token_valid: boolean, expires_at }
- POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/comment
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Body: { text, attachments? }
  - Response: { comment_id, created_at, token_id }
- POST /api/portal/decision/{decision_id}/approve
  - Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>
  - Body: { approved: boolean, comment? }
  - Response: { approval_id, approved, created_at }
- GET /api/portal/link/{token_id}
  - Headers: Optional
  - Response: { token_id, project_id, decision_ids, expires_at, revoked, usage_stats }
- POST /api/portal/link/{token_id}/revoke
  - Response: { revoked: true }
- GET /api/portal/analytics/{token_id}
  - Response: { views, comments, approvals, exports, last_seen_at }
- GET /api/portal/export/{decision_id}
  - Response: { export_url, format, generated_at }

Security
- Authentication: Token-based; no user login required
- Authorization: Actions limited by token scope; validate at server before performing any operation
- Data exposure: Only fields allowed by token scope; minimal data sharing
- Revocation: Immediate token revocation supported; endpoints validate revoked status
- Input/output validation: Server-side strict validation; sanitize all inputs

Validation
- Ensure decision_id and option references exist
- Validate token validity and expiry at every request
- Validate attachment types and sizes
- Enforce maximum comment length and prohibited content checks

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Token-based access works without requiring a login; token is time-limited and scope-limited
- [ ] Decision Detail Page renders correctly with side-by-side option comparison, comments, attachments, and actions
- [ ] Client Portal loads from tokenized link on mobile and desktop with responsive UI
- [ ] Clients can add comments and approve; actions are recorded in analytics with correct token_id
- [ ] Token revocation immediately prevents further access; analytics reflect revocation
- [ ] Exports (PDF/CSV) generated for decisions and include relevant history
- [ ] Access-control errors present clear messages and do not leak internal data
- [ ] UI matches the design system: color palette, typography, spacing, and interactive states
- [ ] End-to-end tests cover: token generation, token usage flow, approval, commenting, export, and revocation

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Focus on clarity, minimalism, and visual decision support
- Ensure high-contrast typography and accessible controls
- Maintain consistent card hierarchy and status indicators
- Use the 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters; generous whitespace
- Maintain left-aligned text and consistent margins/paddings
- Subtle hover/focus states and smooth transitions
- Use the specified color palette for backgrounds, borders, text, and status cues

---

Visual Style

Color Palette:
- Primary background: #F7F7F9
- Secondary background: #FFFFFF
- Accent color: #0052CC
- Neutral grays:
  - #E5E7EB
  - #D1D5DB
  - #6B7280
  - #111827
- Status colors:
  - #10B981 (success/active)
  - #F59E42 (warning)
  - #EF4444 (error/declined)

Typography & Layout:
- Font family: Modern geometric sans-serif (Inter, SF Pro, etc.)
- Headings: H1 ~28px, H2 ~22px, H3 ~18px; weight 600–700
- Body: 15–16px, 400–500; high line-height
- Subt, uppercase/small-caps for labels
- Layout: 12-column grid; 24–32px gutters; clear separation between navigation, cards, content
- Left-aligned text; ample whitespace

Key Design Elements

Card Design:
- Cards: #FFFFFF; shadow 0px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); border-radius 8–12px
- Borders: #E5E7EB
- Hover: lift or tint #F3F4F6
- Hierarchy: Title top, muted secondary info, right-aligned status badge

Navigation:
- Sidebar: Permanent left; background #F5F6FA; active with highlight #E5E7EB or accent underline
- Icons: Minimal line icons; gray #6B7280; active state filled
- Top bar: White with bottom border #E5E7EB
- Collapsible folders: Smooth transitions
- Active items: Bold text, left border or dot in accent

Data Visualization:
- Charts: Minimal; accent color; muted gridlines
- Status indicators: Pills/dots in #10B981, #F59E42, #EF4444

Interactive Elements:
- Buttons: Rounded; primary filled with #0052CC, white text; secondary ghost/outline
- States: Hover shadow, active fill shift, disabled state with opacity
- Form fields: Rounded, borders #D1D5DB, focus ring
- Search bars: Full-width, rounded, left icon
- Micro-interactions: Smooth transitions on hover/focus

Design Philosophy
- Modern, minimalist, professional; calm, readable, structured
- Minimize cognitive load; quick decision-making
- Visual strategy emphasizes readability, whitespace, and clear hierarchy

Connected Pages:
- Decision Detail Page: Full view of a decision card with visual comparison, comments, history, attachments, and actions
- Client Portal (No-Login Link): Mobile-first client view via secure tokenized link; review, compare, comment, and approve without an account

